Here's a simple way to generate the Fibonacci series in Python:
Fibonacci Series Using a Loop
def fibonacci_series(n):
    fib = [0, 1]
    for i in range(2, n):
        fib.append(fib[i-1] + fib[i-2])
    return fib[:n]

# Example: Generate first 10 Fibonacci numbers
print(fibonacci_series(10))
Explanation
•	Starts with [0, 1], the first two Fibonacci numbers.
•	Each new number is the sum of the previous two.
•	n controls how many numbers you want.
Alternative: Using Recursion
def fibonacci_recursive(n):
    if n <= 1:
        return n
    return fibonacci_recursive(n-1) + fibonacci_recursive(n-2)

# Print first 10 Fibonacci numbers
for i in range(10):
    print(fibonacci_recursive(i), end=' ')

